        <body>
            <pb facs="#f0001"/>
            <div n="1">
                <head>
                    <hi rendition="#b">Humboldt and the Letter Writers.</hi>
                </head>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <p>Berlin papers received by the City of Balti-<lb break="no"/>more contain the following card from Alexander<lb break="yes"/>Humboldt.</p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <div n="2">
                    <dateline>
                        <hi rendition="#et">
                            <hi rendition="#k">Berlin,</hi> March 15. 1859.</hi>
                    </dateline>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <p>&#x201C;Suffering beneath the pressure of a still in-<lb break="no"/>creasing correspondence, amounting to between<lb break="yes"/>sixteen hundred and two thousand communica-<lb break="no"/>tions per annum, and embracing letiers, printed<lb break="yes"/>pamphlets on matters with which I am wholly<lb break="yes"/>unacquainted, manuscripts concerning which<lb break="yes" />my opinion is desired, projects for emigration<lb break="yes"/>and colonizing, the sending of models, machines<lb break="yes"/>and natural curiosities, requests of contributions<lb break="yes"/>to collections of autographs, offers to take charge<lb break="yes"/>of my domestic concerns, to cheer and enliven<lb break="yes"/>me &#x0026;c., &#x0026;c., I must again publicly urge all per-<lb break="no"/>sons having my welfare at heart to exert their<lb break="yes"/>influence in my behalf, that individuals in both<lb break="yes"/>continents may no longer busy themselves with<lb break="yes"/>my person and make of my house an intelligence<lb break="yes"/>office; and that I be allowed, in the declining<lb break="yes"/>state of my physical and mental powers, to enjoy<lb break="yes"/>some rest and leisure to attend to my duties<lb break="yes" />May this cry for relief, which I utter with muc@<lb break="yes" />reluctance and after reflection, not meet an un<lb break="yes"/>friendly interpretation!</p>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <closer>
                        <salute>
                            <hi rendition="#et">
                                <hi rendition="#k">alexander von humboldt.</hi>
                            </hi>
                        </salute>
                    </closer>
                </div>
            </div>
            <lb break="yes"/>
        </body>
